 Suppliers



Wacker Chemie AG

                                     •  Plastics & Synthetics                                                                             •  Munich, BV                                                                    

                                    Wacker Chemie AG engages in the manufacturing and distribution of chemical products. It operates through the following segments: Silicones, Polymers, Biosolutions, Polysilicons, Siltronic, and Other. The Silicones segment produces silicones and silicone rubber for consumer goods, chemicals, energy and electronics applications, and construction products. The Polymers segment produces dispersions and dispersible polymer powders. The Biosolutions segment fabricates fine chemicals, such as proteins, cyclodextirins, cysteine, and acetate solid resins. The Polysilicon segment involves hyperpure polysilicon, chlorosilanes, and pyrogenic silicas for the semiconductor and electronics industries. The Siltronic segment includes hyper pure silicon wafers. The Others segments comprises of other activities. The company was founded on October 13, 1914 and is headquartered in Munich, Germany.
                                




OCI Co. Ltd.

                                     •  Semiconductors                                                                             •  Seoul, SL                                                                    

                                    OCI Co., Ltd. engages in the manufacturing and sales of chemical products. It operates through the following business segments: Renewable Energy, Inorganic Chemicals, Fine Chemicals, Insulation, Sapphire Ingot, Petrochemicals and Coal. The Renewable Energy segment offers polysilicon which is the primary raw materials used in the solar PV industry. The Inorganic Chemicals segment products include soda ash, sodium percarbonate, hydrogen peroxide, calcium chloride, sodium chlorate and fumed silica which are essential to a wide range of industries. The Petrochemicals and Coal segment offers a variety of chemical products such as carbon black, toluene di-isocyanate, pitch, benzene, toluene, xylene, phthalic, anhydride, polyol and plasticizer. The Fine Chemicals segment provides an array of chemical reagents and agrochemicals. Its products include phosphoric acid, chemical reagents, nitrogen trifluoride, mono silane, tungsten hexafluoride and silicon filament. The Insulation segment offers insulation materials such as ENERVAC. It was founded on August 5, 1959 and is headquartered in Seoul, South Korea.
                                




centrotherm international AG

                                     •  Electrical Products                                                                             •  Blaubeuren, BV                                                                    

                                    centrotherm international AG engages in developing thermal solutions for the photovoltaic, semiconductor, and microelectronic industries. It operates through the following segments: Silicon, Photovoltaics and Semiconductor, and Thin film and Customized Equipment. The Silicon segment offers engineering, technology and services for integrated process and system packages for polysilicon manufacturing. The Photovoltaics and Semiconductor segment comprises development, construction, production, and sale of individual systems to produce monocrystalline and multicrystalline solar cells. The Thin film and Customized Equipment segment focuses on the development, construction, production, and sale of customized system concepts and special systems for modern coating technologies. The company was founded by Rolf Hans Hartung, Robert Michael Hartung, and Hans Autenrieth on December 28, 2005 and is headquartered in Blaubeuren, Germany.
                                




